                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding notAfter="1700" notBefore="1600">
                        <p>Standard Merton s. xvii, sewn on four bands; chained from the usual position. fols. i-ii, 131–2 are paper binding leaves, the outermost from a larger printed commentary on Terence, s. xv or xvi. An earlier binding had a central strap. fol. iii was a pastedown in an earlier binding.</p>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
